  "texts": [
    "These indexes employ space partitioning and node splitting strategies similar to conventional multidimensional indexes like R-tree and kd-tree, thus inheriting their high generality.",
    "This class of indexes include IF-Index [34] and RSMI [69].Grid-based Index employs grids as the data layout.",
    "Unlike typical grid indexes, learned grid indexes do not physically store grid cells (i.e., partition boundaries); instead, they train learned CDF functions over selected dimensions to locate the appropriate grid cell.",
    "For example, suppose the j-th dimension in the grid index is partitioned into m buckets, a point x will be placed into the cdf j (x j) • m -th bucket, where cdf j (•) ∈ [0, 1] is the CDF function on the j-th dimension of all points.",
    "The grid-based indexes include Flood [58] and Tsunami [21]."
  ],
